<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 375px;"><br/><br>Those all-nighters seem to cause shaky legs. Can you even manage to comprehend after these indefinite halls? Well, you don’t have to!

<br/><br>We’re just a step away from bringing salvation to your journey, but we can assure something beyond a nothingburger!

<br>Want to find out what ‘resting’ is really meant to be? Give us a call from your base or go to the closest Parade building on your site. Our staff is most active on [[Level 399|399]], give it a try!</div></center>

<br/>{{Collapse|num=1|initial=<center><br/><br/><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double black;">[[File:322never.png|375px|center|link=]]</div></center></center>|final=|body=




<br/><br/><br/><br/><div class="quote-noperson">{{Quote|Tranquility? This place looks empty… Am I too early? Or maybe even late? Where's the staff? Anyone…?}}</div>





<br><center><span class="duality">DUALITY</span></center>




<br/><br/><center><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Level_521.png|500px|center|link=]]
</div></center>
</center>

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 500px;"><br><div style="text-align: left>{{Class Custom Image|bg-image=Level_521.png|class=0|safety=Safe|security=Secure|entity=Devoid Of Entities|hexagon=0|text-color=black}}</div></div></center>

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 625px;"><br/>Level 521 is a suburban basement that seemingly goes on for miles; the complex itself remains under-rezoned, with little to no furnishings in each room. Level exhibits a unique characteristic through the interior, with a variety of tables found via the passages. These tables are quite resilient, consisting primarily of furnishing.


Level 521 exhibits 2 distinct regions integrating with each other from time to time; these zones are famously named “Day” and “Night”. Most of the aforementioned information is cited in the “Day” zone, as they make up a significant portion of the level. In contrast, the “Night” zone furnishes make up the sumptuous furnishing of the level.</div></center>

<br/><br/><center><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Noon.png|500px|center|link=]]
</div></center>
</center>

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 625px;"><br/>Level 521’s lacking architecture is often described as unnerving by wanderers, which may cause mild paranoia in the level. Such effects fit within the liminal aspect of the level, as [[Alone]], resulting in pure isolation; one within the level might lose their sanity on prolonged exposure. Although no records of [[Roth Syndrome]] or a [[Phenomenon 35|Wretch]] occurrence happened on the level.


Level 521 lacks communication factors with other levels, making it unsuitable for possible rescue operations. Portrays a paramount risk to lost wanderers, as it lacks proper conditions, mainly due to a lack of food sources. For now, Level 521 is inconvenient for long-term habitation.</div></center>

<br/><br/><center><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Afternoon.png|500px|center|link=]]
</div></center>
</center>

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 625px;"><br/>Level 521’s overall interior remains unexplained, as the lack of communication and total isolation make any information recorded about the level's personal experience, as such expeditions even seem to differ in structural integrity, changing like being multiple floors, “Night” zone being more prominent, and the interior state of design being different per person.


Level 521’s Thresholds seem to be consistent and seldom. Such as the only ingress method being finding, thus accepting a sketchy invitation card of an advertisement for a resting spot by the “Parade”. Furthermore, Egresses, on the other hand, is associated with the tables; seldom do tables within the level have a two-digit number at the top. [[Noclipping]] under a table with a number leads to the associated level, as digits thus only possess slots less than 100, with slots beneath 10 found with 0 for the first digit. The only exception is that, infrequently, a table with party decoration will lead to [[Level Fun]] upon interaction; any other type of egress method seems impossible, even tho exceptional egress has not been found within the “Night” zone; this is theorized to be found at some time.</div></center>




<br/>{{Collapse|num=2|initial=<center><br/><div style="font-size: 50px; font-family: 'Josefin Sans';">???</div></center>|final=|body=



<br><center><span class="ytilaud">DUALITY</span></center>




<br/><br/><center><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Day.png|500px|center|link=]]
</div></center>
</center>

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 375px; font-family: 'Josefin Sans';"><br/><br>


''Disappointed, ain’t ya''


''They promised some relief, a vacation you deserved, and you get hit with… this? What a nothingburger.''


''Seems like theresn’t any exit, “Fucking great,” as you mutter to yourself, you should at least search for some clue, maybe you arrived at the wrong time?''


''You slowly start to get a migraine from this fucking scam, better be quick before you lose your shit.''


''Still, how ironic, isn’t it? You were at your home, not home… but at least it was your place, and now some fuckers dragged you here, “For what?!? WHY!?!”''


''If this is some prank bullshit, then you should’ve seen hints at least? Maybe start to get yourself together, because this isn’t right...''</div></center>




<br/><br/><center><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Bright.png|500px|center|link=]]
</div></center>
</center>

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 375px; font-family: 'Josefin Sans';"><br/><br>


''How long have you been walking?''


''Your life, after entering this damned place…''


''How long have you been traveling around, just to come back to square one?''


''All levels you’ve passed, all encounters you’ve survived…''


''What did you get from it? Did you even have a goal to begin with?''


''Such apathy doesn’t stem from here, you know well.''


''Maybe you’ve just wanted someone who loves, cares, or is part of a community you’ll belong to.''


''Maybe it wasn’t too late after all. Hell, even maybe now…?''


''As you pass each table with such indifference, I think you have started to accept…''


''You could’ve found beauty in towns of [[Level 23|23]].''


''You could’ve found sublimity at [[Level 37|37]].''


''Maybe ask a few questions about [[Level 47|47]]?''


''Maybe even familiarity within [[Level 68|68]].''


''Or even the acceptance within [[Level 92|92]].''


''No, lights shine too bright onto your eyes; these barebones rooms cannot be dealt with anymore…''


''So to subdue your boredom, you took a plunge into the darkness.''</div></center>




<br/><br/><center><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Between.png|500px|center|link=]]
</div></center>
</center>




<br/>{{Collapse|num=3|initial=<center><br/><div style="font-size: 50px; color: crimson; font-family: 'Josefin Sans';">!!!</div></center>|final=|body=

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 375px; font-family: 'Josefin Sans';"><br/><br>


This feels personal…



Darkness already engulfed you in his part; you only see a glimpse of the “Night”, covered with depressing blue walls, other than that, it’s not different from walking in the void. The carpet gets warmer, and you can sense the dampness, nearly as if the walls are pushing on; definitely don’t want to be stuck here.


“Did someone live here?” you ask as more stuff comes around. Even tho you can’t use your sight here, this place feels familiar. This was definitely someone's home, so much stuff lingering around isn’t normal. Did you accidentally come across somebody’s home? Maybe your living space wasn’t bad after all.



As you try to find your way by following the walls, your hand hits something. Is that a light switch? You decide to turn it on…</div></center>


<br/><br/><center><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Dinner.png|500px|center|link=]]
</div></center>
</center>

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 375px; font-family: 'Josefin Sans';"><br/><br>


Lovely dinner, sadly no one here to enjoy…



That hurt? Leaving your family, accepting these rooms as a new home… You always thought you adapted, right? You always thought you could leave your past behind, but even here, your past still remains to follow you. No one knows what might’ve happened to your family; do they still care about you? You do care about them tho, so it should be mutual, right?


A flashlight can be seen with the help of the ceiling light; it doesn’t have much power, but you can still investigate around…


This was more than an ordinary maze; this was home… To someone you don’t know, but it makes sense as this was your life, such sympathy can’t be earned through words; silence was to achieve this. You’re alone with your thoughts.



A bathroom, a bedroom with a 2-person bed, and a few old closets. But one room gets most of your attention, with the last bit of your flashlight's power, you continue…</div></center>


<br/><br/><center><center><div style="display: inline-block; background:rgba (0, 0, 0, 0.8); border: 4px double white;">
[[File:Home.png|500px|center|link=]]
</div></center>
</center>

<center><div style="text-align: justify; max-width: 375px; font-family: 'Josefin Sans';"><br/><br>


That was… That was childhood, at least most of it.


Unexpected? You begin to sob, closing your eyes as tightly as you can; you don't want to deal with any of this. How much time have you spent there? That was home...


How long have you cried? Your flashlight is already dead, so you drop it on the floor and walk slowly. You are no longer stressed. You feel as calm as possible. You have survived yourself, and now you accept who you are.


Now you know why this was a parade. As you predicted, the exit sign glows its crimson onto your face; it’s time to face what you’ve needed to face, to admire what all of this is for, to admire the precious side of living for…</div></center>


